The paper focuses on program analysis tasks such as program synthesis, program repair, and fault localization, which are typically studied in the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper proposes a novel semantic program embedding that is learned from program execution traces, which involves the use of Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) to model sequential program states. This suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The paper also evaluates the proposed embedding on predicting errors in student submissions to an introductory programming class and exercises on the CodeHunt education platform, indicating a potential connection to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and education (cs.EDU) sub-categories.
